class SORTracker {
public:
    SORTracker() {
        idx = 0;
    }

    void add(string name, int score) {
        pq.push({score, name});
    }

    string get() {
        for (int i = 0; i < idx; i++) {
            pq.pop();
        }
        idx++;
        string res = pq.top().second;
        pq.pop();
        return res;
    }
private:
    priority_queue<pair<int, string>, vector<pair<int, string>>, less<pair<int, string>>> pq;
    int idx;
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a priority queue to store the scenic locations. The priority queue is ordered by the score in descending order and the name in ascending order. The `add` method adds a new location to the priority queue. The `get` method returns the `i`th best location by popping the top `i-1` elements from the priority queue and returning the top element.

